name: Blacka Di Danca
tweet: So now more than ever... is the time to absolutely not lower the value of artists, but to highlight it

name: Blacka Di Danca
tweet: Anyway you flip it... every human in a comfortable home is filling up their day with a higher level of consumption from an artist‚Äôs work. Actors who acted in the Netflix shows... dancers online... authors who wrote the books... chef‚Äôs on your favorite cooking show...

name: Blacka Di Danca
tweet: Everyone is either reading, watching tv, meditating, listening to music, binge watching on Netflix or Hulu or whatever, taking dance classes online or watching their favorite YouTube choreographies...

name: Blacka Di Danca
tweet: And now... more than ever. The world can finally realize the true value of an artist. Because now, more than ever... artists are on top of the pyramid. Let me tell you why.

name: Blacka Di Danca
tweet: I believe in creatives. I believe in art. And I highly value anyone brave enough to put their heart out there in the world to judge - disguised in the form of a song or a dance routine. I highly value the artist.

name: Blacka Di Danca
tweet: Not because we don‚Äôt understand that people are out of work, but because we do. Because we are also those people out of work, and value doesn‚Äôt change, only circumstances.

name: Blacka Di Danca
tweet: And we charge for our online classes

tweet: So I moved everyone into an air bnb that we‚Äôve been renting every single week since March 16th to teach online workshops out of through my talent agency @dancaagency. We live together, self-quarantined, eating, sharing, sleeping, dancing, monetizing‚úäüèæ
